COVID-19 Status

As of 8:50PM PT yesterday, over 1.4 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 26.6 thousand have died.

In the last day, 466 new infections were reported and 6 deaths. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 48 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 80.4% have their 1st shot and 63.5% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is speeding up, but there are 8.2 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~25 days for new deliveries to get into arms. At the current rate, all Canadians aged 12+ will have the first dose by Dec-25 and fully vaccinated by 2022-Jan-22. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
